@startuml
title SensibLaw / ITIR World-Model Metasystem\nUpdated 2026-05-06

top to bottom direction

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName SansSerif
skinparam wrapWidth 150
skinparam maxMessageSize 120
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 8
}

legend bottom
Current posture: bounded review and projection, not global truth or edit authority.
The April lane sketch has been replaced by the current normalized substrate:
canonical text -> PNF/typed carriers -> residual/pressure -> governed artifacts.
endlegend

rectangle "Source + Observation Families" as SOURCES {
  component "Canonical documents\nPDF / HTML / JSON / transcript" as CANON_SRC
  component "Wikidata / Wikipedia\nbounded graph + text slices" as WIKI_SRC
  component "WorldMonitor\nexternal observation source" as WM_SRC
  component "OpenRecall\ninternal observation source" as OR_SRC
  component "Legal / narrative lanes\nAU, affidavit, GWB, Brexit" as LEGAL_SRC
  component "Future bounded producers" as FUTURE_SRC
}

rectangle "Adapter + Canonicalization Layer" as ADAPTERS {
  component "Media adapters\nsource provenance only" as MEDIA_ADAPT
  component "Canonical text substrate\none parser spine" as CANON_TEXT
  component "Extraction profiles\nnormative_policy and domain profiles" as PROFILES
  component "Observation substrate\nWM + OpenRecall normalized together" as OBS_SUB
  component "Grounding catalogs\nQID / PID / closure paths" as GROUNDING
}

rectangle "Typed Predicate / PNF Substrate" as PNF {
  component "Predicate extraction" as PRED_EXTRACT
  component "Role binding\nsubject / object / qualifiers / wrapper" as ROLE_BIND
  component "Predicate-normal-form carriers\nroles + qualifiers + provenance" as PNF_CARRIER
  component "Soft type inference\nfrom role, participation, context" as SOFT_TYPE
  component "Residual lattice\nexact / partial / no_typed_meet / contradiction" as RESIDUAL
  component "Pressure index\nlocal, upstream, sibling, downstream,\ntemporal/mereology, metaclass, disjointness" as PRESSURE
}

rectangle "World-Model Control Plane" as CONTROL {
  component "Cross-domain claim model\nminimal Phi atoms" as PHI
  component "Composed candidate nodes\nabove Phi" as CANDIDATES
  component "Admissibility gates\nfail-closed node + edge checks" as GATES
  component "Temporal update discipline\nrevision/window/snapshot aware" as TEMPORAL
  component "Contradiction management\nhold vs repair vs promote" as CONFLICT
  component "Unified action policy\nreview-first, receipt-gated" as POLICY
}

rectangle "Implemented Bounded Lanes" as LANES {
  component "Wikidata migration packs\nP5991 -> P14143 climate lane" as MIGRATION
  component "ChangeReviewPacket harness\ncandidate repair comparison\nQ27968055 / P31 / P279" as CHANGE_REVIEW
  component "Disjointness + hotspot packs\nP2738 / P11260 / structural clusters" as HOTSPOTS
  component "Temporal PNF contract\nclimate + mereology preconditions" as TEMP_PNF
  component "Semantic memory helper\nprivate retrieval records\nfrom atoms + groundings" as SEM_MEMORY
  component "Legal follow graph\nadditive pressure metadata" as LEGAL_FOLLOW
  component "Market-news predicate projector\nevidence-only PredicateAtom output" as MARKET_NEWS
}

rectangle "ITIR MCP / Projection Boundary" as MCP {
  component "itir-mcp registry\nnamespaced bounded tools" as MCP_REG
  component "SensibLaw adapters\nobligations + review surfaces" as MCP_SL
  component "Observation comparison\ncompare / score / envelope" as MCP_OBS
  component "Docstore tools\nstatus + open questions" as DOCSTORE
  component "Obsidian observer\ncandidate hints only" as OBSIDIAN
  component "Markdown projections\nreplaceable generated pages" as MARKDOWN
  component "Bridge safe_call\nclassification + verification + receipt" as SAFE_CALL
}

rectangle "Governed Outputs" as OUTPUTS {
  component "Review packets / reports\ncandidate-only, reviewable,\nheld, promotable" as REVIEW
  component "OpenRefine / checked-safe CSV\nstaging artifact only" as CSV
  component "Split plans / obligations\nexternal governance receipt required" as SPLIT
  component "Operator queues + indexes\nCohort B/C/D/E and governance summaries" as OPERATOR
  component "Audit / provenance trace\nreceipts, reasons, after-state checks" as AUDIT
  component "Downstream handoff artifacts\nZelph / StatiBaker / external reviewers" as HANDOFF
}

CANON_SRC --> MEDIA_ADAPT
LEGAL_SRC --> MEDIA_ADAPT
WIKI_SRC --> GROUNDING
WIKI_SRC --> MEDIA_ADAPT
WM_SRC --> OBS_SUB
OR_SRC --> OBS_SUB
FUTURE_SRC --> MEDIA_ADAPT

MEDIA_ADAPT --> CANON_TEXT
CANON_TEXT --> PROFILES
PROFILES --> PRED_EXTRACT
OBS_SUB --> PRED_EXTRACT
GROUNDING --> SOFT_TYPE

PRED_EXTRACT --> ROLE_BIND
ROLE_BIND --> PNF_CARRIER
PNF_CARRIER --> SOFT_TYPE
SOFT_TYPE --> RESIDUAL
RESIDUAL --> PRESSURE

PNF_CARRIER --> PHI
RESIDUAL --> CANDIDATES
PRESSURE --> CANDIDATES
PHI --> CANDIDATES
CANDIDATES --> GATES
GATES --> TEMPORAL
TEMPORAL --> CONFLICT
CONFLICT --> POLICY

WIKI_SRC --> MIGRATION
WIKI_SRC --> CHANGE_REVIEW
WIKI_SRC --> HOTSPOTS
PNF_CARRIER --> TEMP_PNF
GROUNDING --> SEM_MEMORY
PHI --> LEGAL_FOLLOW
PNF_CARRIER --> MARKET_NEWS

MIGRATION --> REVIEW
MIGRATION --> CSV
MIGRATION --> SPLIT
CHANGE_REVIEW --> REVIEW
HOTSPOTS --> REVIEW
TEMP_PNF --> GATES
SEM_MEMORY --> DOCSTORE
LEGAL_FOLLOW --> OPERATOR
MARKET_NEWS --> REVIEW

POLICY --> REVIEW
POLICY --> CSV
POLICY --> SPLIT
POLICY --> OPERATOR
POLICY --> AUDIT
POLICY --> HANDOFF

REVIEW --> MCP_SL
OPERATOR --> MCP_SL
OBS_SUB --> MCP_OBS
AUDIT --> DOCSTORE
REVIEW --> DOCSTORE
DOCSTORE --> OBSIDIAN
DOCSTORE --> MARKDOWN
MCP_SL --> MCP_REG
MCP_OBS --> MCP_REG
DOCSTORE --> MCP_REG
MCP_REG --> SAFE_CALL
SAFE_CALL --> AUDIT
MARKDOWN --> HANDOFF

note right of WIKI_SRC
Current Wikidata mode:
- bounded graph/text slices
- migration packs
- PNF/residual demonstrator
- hotspot and disjointness reports
- ChangeReviewPacket comparison
- no blind edit authority
end note

note right of CHANGE_REVIEW
Current repair-comparison harness:
- mutates bounded slices in memory
- compares candidate diagnostics
- attributes pressure by component
- emits review-only dispositions
end note

note right of SEM_MEMORY
Semantic memory is deterministic and private:
it consumes supplied atoms, grounding rows,
and ontology closure paths. It is not an
entity linker and does not promote truth.
end note

note bottom of POLICY
Governance boundary:
tool findings, LLM suggestions, subclass checks,
constraints, and disjointness signals are candidate
evidence. Only locally complete checked-safe rows
move to governed staging, and community or downstream
authority still decides desirability.
end note

note bottom of MCP
MCP is a projection and adapter boundary.
It exposes bounded tools and generated pages
without taking canonical ownership from
SensibLaw, StatiBaker, Wikidata lanes, or
other producers.
end note

@enduml
